# =============================================================================
# üß™ TESTNET CONFIGURATION (Celo Sepolia) - Default for Development
# =============================================================================

# Server Configuration
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000

# Testnet Payment Configuration
PAYMENT_WALLET_ADDRESS=0xYourWalletAddressHere
NETWORK=celo-sepolia
PAYMENT_PRICE_USD=0.001
FACILITATOR_URL=http://localhost:3005

# =============================================================================
# üöÄ MAINNET CONFIGURATION (Celo) - For Production Deployment
# =============================================================================
#
# To use mainnet, uncomment these lines and comment out testnet config above:
#
# NODE_ENV=production
# PORT=3000
# PAYMENT_WALLET_ADDRESS=0xYourProductionWalletAddress
# NETWORK=celo
# PAYMENT_PRICE_USD=0.01
# FACILITATOR_URL=http://localhost:3005

# =============================================================================
# Vercel Deployment Variables (automatically set by Vercel)
# =============================================================================
VERCEL=
VERCEL_ENV=

# =============================================================================
# üìù SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
#
# üß™ TESTNET SETUP (celo-sepolia) - Recommended for Development:
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Use the TESTNET configuration (already set above as default)
# 3. Set PAYMENT_WALLET_ADDRESS to your wallet address
# 4. NETWORK is already set to celo-sepolia (testnet)
# 5. IMPORTANT: Start the CeloFacilitator:
#    - cd ../CeloFacilitator
#    - npm run dev (runs on port 3005)
# 6. Get testnet USDC on Celo Sepolia:
#    - Visit: https://faucet.celo.org/
#    - Get testnet CELO, then swap for USDC on Uniswap
#    - USDC Contract: 0x01C5C0122039549AD1493B8220cABEdD739BC44E
# 7. Test your API:
#    - Start server: npm run dev
#    - Test the demo endpoint at GET /api/demo
#
# ‚úÖ Testnet Benefits:
#    - Free USDC for testing (via faucet + swap)
#    - No CDP API keys required
#    - Same functionality as mainnet
#    - Safe environment for development
#    - Uses local CeloFacilitator on port 3005
#
# üöÄ MAINNET SETUP (celo) - For Production:
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. In .env file, comment out testnet config and uncomment mainnet config
# 2. Set NETWORK=celo
# 3. Set PAYMENT_WALLET_ADDRESS to production wallet (separate from testnet!)
# 4. Ensure CeloFacilitator is running with mainnet configuration
# 5. Buy USDC on Celo network for client testing
# 6. Deploy to production server with CeloFacilitator
# 7. Test production deployment
#
# ‚ö†Ô∏è Mainnet Important Notes:
#    - Use separate wallet addresses for testnet and mainnet
#    - Real USDC payments will be processed
#    - Test thoroughly on testnet before going to mainnet
#    - Monitor your wallet for incoming payments
#    - Ensure CeloFacilitator is configured for Celo mainnet
#
# üîÑ SWITCHING BETWEEN ENVIRONMENTS:
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Simply change the NETWORK variable in your .env file:
# - NETWORK=celo-sepolia (testnet)
# - NETWORK=celo (mainnet)
#
# The template automatically:
# - Detects the network from .env
# - Connects to CeloFacilitator on port 3005
# - Enables Bazaar discovery only in production (NODE_ENV=production or VERCEL=1)
